sections.text:
The State shall provide and assign office space and the necessary equipment and supplies for the Register in Chancery Office in each county of the State and whenever occasion requires, may change such space and assign different space.73 Del. Laws
§

 7;

The Register in Chancery Office shall be open in each county each day except legal holidays, Saturdays and Sundays.73 Del. Laws, c. 91,
§

 7;
